modules.description: Enumerates values of a variant type, generating a list of all possible constructors. Works with algebraic data types defined in OCaml, particularly sum types. Useful for testing, serialization, or generating exhaustive cases in pattern matching.

This module defines interfaces for enumerating values of various type arities, supporting operations to list all possible values of a type. It works with polymorphic variants, sum types, and higher-kinded types through its multiple signature types. Concrete use cases include generating test cases for all variants of a type or implementing exhaustive pattern matching utilities.

This module provides functions to enumerate all possible values of a type, including support for polymorphic variants, sum types, and higher-kinded types. It enables concrete use cases such as generating exhaustive test cases and building pattern matching utilities. The operations are structured through multiple signatures that define enumeration interfaces for different type arities.
